1
00:00:22,464 --> 00:00:26,432
♪Should we forget yesterday's sorrows♪

2
00:00:26,432 --> 00:00:29,728
♪And the dazed confusion♪

3
00:00:30,976 --> 00:00:33,681
♪Should we let go of♪

4
00:00:33,681 --> 00:00:35,904
♪The stubborn madness♪

5
00:00:35,904 --> 00:00:39,072
♪And naive recklessness now♪

6
00:00:40,192 --> 00:00:43,840
♪Those years, those faces♪

7
00:00:44,992 --> 00:00:48,763
♪Those old scars we can't erase♪

8
00:00:49,824 --> 00:00:52,460
♪Tears streaming, facing the light♪

9
00:00:53,152 --> 00:00:57,594
♪Piercing the sorrow within♪

10
00:01:08,716 --> 00:01:12,736
♪The road ahead's long,
stumbling all the way♪

11
00:01:13,536 --> 00:01:18,076
♪The wounds we've borne
are medals hidden within♪

12
00:01:18,336 --> 00:01:22,391
♪Standing alone on an open plain♪

13
00:01:23,168 --> 00:01:26,851
♪We gaze at the stars♪

14
00:01:31,228 --> 00:01:34,816
=The Dream Maker=

15
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,735
=Episode 31=

16
00:01:38,386 --> 00:01:39,266
When did you get here?

17
00:01:39,546 --> 00:01:40,225
(Yan's Wontons)
When?

18
00:01:40,505 --> 00:01:41,505
You hear everything?

19
00:01:41,585 --> 00:01:42,266
What do you want?

20
00:01:43,065 --> 00:01:46,026
Well, I want to buy a karaoke machine.

21
00:01:46,345 --> 00:01:47,345
What machine?

22
00:01:48,186 --> 00:01:50,225
Master, that karaoke machine

23
00:01:50,505 --> 00:01:52,466
is something
that can be used for singing.

24
00:01:56,266 --> 00:01:57,425
A singing machine?

25
00:01:57,666 --> 00:01:58,166
Yes.

26
00:01:58,225 --> 00:02:00,585
Then it's similar to a guitar, right?

27
00:02:01,026 --> 00:02:02,145
- Guitar?
- No.

28
00:02:02,546 --> 00:02:04,425
It's more advanced than a guitar, right?

29
00:02:04,785 --> 00:02:05,945
You can sing with it.

30
00:02:06,225 --> 00:02:07,986
There's a...

31
00:02:08,145 --> 00:02:09,826
It can play by itself.

32
00:02:10,106 --> 00:02:11,066
You'll figure it out.

33
00:02:11,226 --> 00:02:12,066
Otherwise...

34
00:02:12,305 --> 00:02:13,666
It's okay or it's not.

35
00:02:13,826 --> 00:02:14,826
Anyway, see if it's okay.

36
00:02:14,946 --> 00:02:15,446
Right?

37
00:02:15,506 --> 00:02:16,266
You tell him.

38
00:02:16,346 --> 00:02:17,266
He doesn't know it.

39
00:02:17,666 --> 00:02:18,786
Well, Dongfu.

40
00:02:19,106 --> 00:02:21,546
I delivered goods
to the Yuehai Grand Hotel this morning.

41
00:02:21,865 --> 00:02:22,666
I saw they had

42
00:02:22,826 --> 00:02:24,465
a karaoke machine.

43
00:02:24,465 --> 00:02:25,405
- Yan.
- I...

44
00:02:25,666 --> 00:02:26,346
Buy it.

45
00:02:26,745 --> 00:02:28,745
As long as you like it, buy one.

46
00:02:50,738 --> 00:02:52,465
(Chunmei Printery)

47
00:02:52,465 --> 00:02:54,106
You helped a lot today.

48
00:02:54,525 --> 00:02:56,152
Thanks for introducing me to Mr. Zhang,

49
00:02:56,386 --> 00:02:58,145
or I couldn't land this order.

50
00:02:58,546 --> 00:02:59,185
Not at all.

51
00:02:59,705 --> 00:03:01,226
I thought to have dinner with you,

52
00:03:01,266 --> 00:03:02,946
but I have something to do. Another day.

53
00:03:03,106 --> 00:03:03,606
Okay.

54
00:03:03,745 --> 00:03:04,546
- I'll leave.
- Yuan.

55
00:03:04,745 --> 00:03:05,245
Thanks.

56
00:03:05,286 --> 00:03:06,145
- Not at all.
- Bye.

57
00:03:06,145 --> 00:03:06,645
Take care.

58
00:03:10,866 --> 00:03:11,960
(Chunmei Printery Welcomes You)

59
00:03:16,425 --> 00:03:17,066
Mr. Qian.

60
00:03:18,865 --> 00:03:19,546
Wait for me?

61
00:03:22,745 --> 00:03:23,705
Been waiting here?

62
00:03:23,946 --> 00:03:24,546
Yes.

63
00:03:26,066 --> 00:03:27,625
What if I leave through the back door?

64
00:03:27,946 --> 00:03:28,946
Then I'll wait there.

65
00:03:31,066 --> 00:03:32,585
If I intentionally avoid you,

66
00:03:32,585 --> 00:03:34,465
would I let you know that?

67
00:03:36,145 --> 00:03:37,826
If I were you, I would've rushed in,

68
00:03:38,106 --> 00:03:39,946
pestering, making a scene,
and threatening.

69
00:03:40,106 --> 00:03:42,745
You should've ruined my business
until I agree to teach you.

70
00:03:44,546 --> 00:03:46,386
So, to get something done,

71
00:03:46,905 --> 00:03:48,346
you can't only rely on persistence.

72
00:03:48,946 --> 00:03:51,425
Use tricks when necessary, understand?

73
00:03:51,905 --> 00:03:53,705
I understand. Thank you, sir.

74
00:03:53,986 --> 00:03:55,705
- What did you call me?
- Sir.

75
00:03:57,145 --> 00:03:57,826
Mr. Qian.

76
00:03:58,625 --> 00:03:59,305
Call me Master.

77
00:04:03,786 --> 00:04:04,546
Master.

78
00:04:06,266 --> 00:04:06,766
Alright.

79
00:04:07,066 --> 00:04:09,066
Have dinner with me tonight
to meet a client.

80
00:04:09,826 --> 00:04:10,585
But first,

81
00:04:10,946 --> 00:04:12,386
you have to change your clothes.

82
00:04:12,745 --> 00:04:14,826
As the saying goes,
"Clothes make the man."

83
00:04:15,025 --> 00:04:17,466
First impressions are very important.

84
00:04:17,606 --> 00:04:18,986
If you're dressed so shabbily,

85
00:04:19,265 --> 00:04:20,666
they won't even talk to you.

86
00:04:24,745 --> 00:04:25,666
Right here?

87
00:04:29,986 --> 00:04:30,825
It fits quite well.

88
00:04:34,026 --> 00:04:34,745
What's up, Master?

89
00:04:35,305 --> 00:04:36,586
Don't be so tense.

90
00:04:36,586 --> 00:04:37,625
Come on, turn around.

91
00:04:39,825 --> 00:04:40,745
Xiaohai, remember.

92
00:04:41,466 --> 00:04:43,786
If you're not good with words,
then play to your strengths.

93
00:04:44,666 --> 00:04:46,546
Speak less, observe more.

94
00:04:47,106 --> 00:04:48,065
When you're with me,

95
00:04:48,305 --> 00:04:49,906
you have to know what I want to do

96
00:04:50,505 --> 00:04:51,586
with just one look from me.

97
00:04:51,865 --> 00:04:53,505
Well, what do I want to do now?

98
00:04:56,865 --> 00:04:57,986
You want to...

99
00:04:58,706 --> 00:04:59,305
Now you...

100
00:04:59,346 --> 00:05:00,346
Enough. You'll learn.

101
00:05:01,146 --> 00:05:02,305
What matters most now

102
00:05:03,185 --> 00:05:04,586
is to relax.

103
00:05:04,825 --> 00:05:06,586
Relax. Don't look so serious.

104
00:05:07,226 --> 00:05:07,945
Smile.

105
00:05:12,466 --> 00:05:13,065
One more.

106
00:05:18,146 --> 00:05:19,305
Okay, pretty good.

107
00:05:21,146 --> 00:05:24,305
This haircut should last a month or so.

108
00:05:25,346 --> 00:05:25,906
Okay.

109
00:05:30,265 --> 00:05:30,865
Lili.

110
00:05:32,425 --> 00:05:34,226
Did you paint this picture?

111
00:05:34,825 --> 00:05:35,986
Yes, I painted it.

112
00:05:36,865 --> 00:05:37,666
You painted it?

113
00:05:37,706 --> 00:05:38,385
Yes.

114
00:05:47,546 --> 00:05:48,305
What is this?

115
00:05:48,906 --> 00:05:49,865
I made it.

116
00:05:50,305 --> 00:05:51,865
You can press the button over there.

117
00:05:52,026 --> 00:05:52,825
After you press it,

118
00:05:52,825 --> 00:05:54,425
it'll really move

119
00:05:54,425 --> 00:05:55,425
like a record player.

120
00:05:55,745 --> 00:05:56,666
Really.

121
00:05:57,226 --> 00:05:57,865
Fun, right?

122
00:05:58,385 --> 00:06:00,786
Lili, I only knew
you were great at drawing.

123
00:06:00,906 --> 00:06:03,106
Didn't expect your crafts
to be this amazing too.

124
00:06:04,185 --> 00:06:05,706
Business at the salon has been slow.

125
00:06:06,106 --> 00:06:07,786
I made these to kill time.

126
00:06:07,945 --> 00:06:08,865
Keep it if you like it.

127
00:06:09,026 --> 00:06:09,706
No way.

128
00:06:10,385 --> 00:06:12,664
You must have put a lot of thought
into making this.

129
00:06:12,925 --> 00:06:13,706
I'll pay for it.

130
00:06:14,546 --> 00:06:15,425
No need.

131
00:06:15,445 --> 00:06:16,825
I just made these to kill time.

132
00:06:16,945 --> 00:06:18,786
I can make one anytime.

133
00:06:19,226 --> 00:06:21,625
Look, I made all of these.

134
00:06:21,986 --> 00:06:22,625
And these.

135
00:06:25,106 --> 00:06:26,146
I made this from junk.

136
00:06:28,706 --> 00:06:29,906
You're so creative.

137
00:06:30,586 --> 00:06:33,425
And this one. I made it with shells.

138
00:06:33,546 --> 00:06:34,786
I picked shells up myself.

139
00:06:34,945 --> 00:06:37,425
This is a bunny, and here's a bird.
Cute, right?

140
00:06:37,906 --> 00:06:38,906
So creative.

141
00:06:39,226 --> 00:06:40,625
Look how fun those eyes are.

142
00:06:43,986 --> 00:06:44,486
And this.

143
00:06:44,625 --> 00:06:45,146
Look,

144
00:06:46,106 --> 00:06:47,026
I painted these.

145
00:06:47,625 --> 00:06:49,185
I paint when I have free time.

146
00:06:49,666 --> 00:06:50,425
Take a look.

147
00:06:51,305 --> 00:06:52,666
Too many to keep up.

148
00:06:52,706 --> 00:06:53,346
Look from here.

149
00:06:53,625 --> 00:06:55,226
The paint will dirty your hands.

150
00:06:55,385 --> 00:06:55,885
Okay.

151
00:06:59,026 --> 00:07:00,305
Did you design all of these?

152
00:07:01,906 --> 00:07:04,065
You're practically China's Picasso.

153
00:07:05,146 --> 00:07:05,646
Who?

154
00:07:05,865 --> 00:07:07,625
A great artist, very unconventional.

155
00:07:07,945 --> 00:07:08,906
A great artist?

156
00:07:10,346 --> 00:07:13,106
I'll bring you one of his art books.

157
00:07:13,586 --> 00:07:14,825
It will surely open your eyes.

158
00:07:15,226 --> 00:07:17,666
Alright, I'll take a good look

159
00:07:18,786 --> 00:07:21,265
at P-Picasso.

160
00:07:25,906 --> 00:07:26,666
Ms. Li.

161
00:07:28,986 --> 00:07:30,865
Do you really think
the things I made are good?

162
00:07:32,185 --> 00:07:34,906
Very good! Unrestrained and creative!

163
00:07:38,825 --> 00:07:40,026
Do you think others

164
00:07:40,906 --> 00:07:42,945
would also think
the things I made are good?

165
00:07:44,305 --> 00:07:46,106
Who are you referring to?

166
00:07:49,026 --> 00:07:50,305
Money's on the table.

167
00:07:50,825 --> 00:07:51,325
Got it.

168
00:07:51,825 --> 00:07:52,546
See you next time.

169
00:07:53,026 --> 00:07:53,526
Okay.

170
00:08:00,850 --> 00:08:05,330
(Yan's Wontons)

171
00:08:07,945 --> 00:08:10,185
You're here. Take a seat.
I'll make you some wontons.

172
00:08:10,466 --> 00:08:11,265
No, no need.

173
00:08:13,625 --> 00:08:14,226
What's wrong?

174
00:08:16,745 --> 00:08:18,106
Take this.

175
00:08:18,346 --> 00:08:19,065
Keep this.

176
00:08:19,786 --> 00:08:20,666
What is it?

177
00:08:24,466 --> 00:08:27,265
That machine you want?

178
00:08:28,146 --> 00:08:29,546
It must be expensive.

179
00:08:31,466 --> 00:08:32,745
Just take it.

180
00:08:38,025 --> 00:08:39,306
No, I can't take your money.

181
00:08:39,346 --> 00:08:39,865
Take it back.

182
00:08:39,946 --> 00:08:40,865
Why do you reject?

183
00:08:40,865 --> 00:08:41,706
Take it, you keep it.

184
00:08:41,706 --> 00:08:42,946
I can't take it. Listen.

185
00:08:43,145 --> 00:08:43,645
Don't.

186
00:08:43,706 --> 00:08:44,505
Don't do this.

187
00:08:44,986 --> 00:08:45,865
There are people here.

188
00:08:45,865 --> 00:08:46,785
- Many people are here...
- You...

189
00:08:47,865 --> 00:08:48,826
Keep it.

190
00:08:53,066 --> 00:08:53,586
You...

191
00:08:54,505 --> 00:08:55,306
Take care.

192
00:09:03,922 --> 00:09:07,250
(Lili's Hair Salon)

193
00:09:17,816 --> 00:09:21,924
♪My heart is clear to see♪

194
00:09:23,706 --> 00:09:26,025
Don't move or I'll cut your ear.

195
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:30,712
♪My heart was once broken by love♪

196
00:09:30,808 --> 00:09:35,788
♪Why do sweet dreams end so easily♪

197
00:09:36,216 --> 00:09:39,858
♪You have gentle eyes♪

198
00:09:43,265 --> 00:09:44,385
I'm leaving tomorrow.

199
00:09:46,505 --> 00:09:47,066
Where to?

200
00:09:48,145 --> 00:09:48,905
Everywhere.

201
00:09:49,706 --> 00:09:52,025
As a salesman, I need to travel around.

202
00:09:53,306 --> 00:09:53,946
By the way,

203
00:09:54,346 --> 00:09:56,346
I've passed Changyuan's test

204
00:09:56,665 --> 00:09:57,625
and he is my master now.

205
00:09:57,706 --> 00:09:59,826
Really? Wonderful!

206
00:10:00,986 --> 00:10:02,545
Actually, I have to thank you.

207
00:10:03,066 --> 00:10:05,426
No need. You did well yourself.

208
00:10:06,346 --> 00:10:09,186
Learn hard from Changyuan. Go for it!

209
00:10:09,706 --> 00:10:10,265
Go for it!

210
00:10:13,624 --> 00:10:17,077
♪Your heart is clear to see♪

211
00:10:20,665 --> 00:10:21,905
Don't move, okay?

212
00:10:22,545 --> 00:10:23,545
I won't move.

213
00:10:26,665 --> 00:10:27,226
What?

214
00:10:33,186 --> 00:10:34,785
(Guanhai Terrace, Yuehai, Pingchuan)
Lili, I've thought it all over.

215
00:10:35,306 --> 00:10:36,145
This is a beginning.

216
00:10:36,545 --> 00:10:39,106
Wherever I go, I'll send you a postcard.

217
00:10:41,106 --> 00:10:43,794
(When you feel sad, watch the sunrise.
It will warm your heart.)

218
00:10:48,145 --> 00:10:49,946
This is my favorite spot in Yuehai.

219
00:10:52,665 --> 00:10:54,066
Especially Mr. Zheng's words on it.

220
00:10:56,905 --> 00:10:57,826
Thank you.

221
00:11:05,426 --> 00:11:06,826
I won't be gone for long.

222
00:11:07,625 --> 00:11:09,426
I'll be back once a month.

223
00:11:11,186 --> 00:11:12,586
You have Grandma to take care of.

224
00:11:13,745 --> 00:11:14,426
Yes.

225
00:11:17,848 --> 00:11:21,464
♪My heart was once broken by love♪

226
00:11:21,646 --> 00:11:26,744
♪Why do sweet dreams end so easily♪

227
00:11:30,106 --> 00:11:31,905
Are you okay?

228
00:11:41,426 --> 00:11:42,545
I've fallen for someone.

229
00:11:53,505 --> 00:11:54,865
Who...

230
00:11:55,865 --> 00:11:56,665
Who is it?

231
00:12:02,793 --> 00:12:07,165
♪My heart is clear to see♪

232
00:12:07,454 --> 00:12:11,466
♪Longing for a true love♪

233
00:12:11,466 --> 00:12:12,106
If...

234
00:12:13,346 --> 00:12:14,706
If you like him,

235
00:12:15,986 --> 00:12:17,066
you should tell him.

236
00:12:18,186 --> 00:12:20,226
But I don't know if he likes me.

237
00:12:20,466 --> 00:12:21,466
He must like you.

238
00:12:21,466 --> 00:12:25,392
♪You have gentle eyes♪

239
00:12:25,944 --> 00:12:29,910
♪You have an understanding heart♪

240
00:12:30,488 --> 00:12:32,545
♪If you're willing♪

241
00:12:32,545 --> 00:12:34,265
I-I mean...

242
00:12:36,066 --> 00:12:36,706
I...

243
00:12:36,706 --> 00:12:38,466
I mean, you're so pretty.

244
00:12:40,385 --> 00:12:41,385
He must like you.

245
00:12:44,466 --> 00:12:48,226
♪I'm a lonely girl♪

246
00:12:48,226 --> 00:12:49,785
But if I tell him,

247
00:12:50,986 --> 00:12:52,145
will he like me?

248
00:12:53,682 --> 00:12:57,790
♪No more crying until dawn♪

249
00:12:59,586 --> 00:13:00,706
You could try.

250
00:13:02,930 --> 00:13:06,628
♪Longing for a true love♪

251
00:13:07,032 --> 00:13:11,357
♪My heart was once broken by love♪

252
00:13:13,106 --> 00:13:14,145
Don't move!

253
00:13:21,586 --> 00:13:22,552
(Chats under 5 minutes)
Mr. Zheng,

254
00:13:22,552 --> 00:13:24,665
we've been in Yuehai for five months.

255
00:13:24,905 --> 00:13:26,904
My child's school registration
isn't settled yet.

256
00:13:27,544 --> 00:13:30,326
Alright then, I'll write you a note.

257
00:13:30,545 --> 00:13:31,426
Thank you, Mr. Zheng.

258
00:13:32,826 --> 00:13:33,326
Here.

259
00:13:33,405 --> 00:13:33,905
Thank you.

260
00:13:33,905 --> 00:13:34,405
Take this.

261
00:13:34,665 --> 00:13:35,226
Thank you.

262
00:13:35,265 --> 00:13:36,385
Not at all. It's my duty.

263
00:13:47,025 --> 00:13:47,986
Do you remember me?

264
00:13:50,306 --> 00:13:51,306
You're...

265
00:13:51,426 --> 00:13:51,986
I am...

266
00:13:53,306 --> 00:13:53,806
Wang...

267
00:13:53,986 --> 00:13:54,665
Wang Lili.

268
00:13:55,066 --> 00:13:55,566
Yes.

269
00:13:56,025 --> 00:13:57,306
- Wang Lili.
- Wang Lili.

270
00:13:57,466 --> 00:13:58,385
Yes! Exactly.

271
00:14:01,025 --> 00:14:01,545
What's wrong?

272
00:14:02,025 --> 00:14:03,265
I have a question for you.

273
00:14:03,986 --> 00:14:04,486
Go ahead.

274
00:14:06,826 --> 00:14:07,706
It's a clock I made.

275
00:14:08,145 --> 00:14:09,986
I enjoy doing crafts in my spare time.

276
00:14:10,346 --> 00:14:11,106
I made this.

277
00:14:11,946 --> 00:14:12,446
Look.

278
00:14:13,265 --> 00:14:14,265
A small jewelry box.

279
00:14:14,505 --> 00:14:17,706
My family says
this hobby wastes my time.

280
00:14:18,066 --> 00:14:19,306
So I wanted to ask you,

281
00:14:19,865 --> 00:14:22,946
do you think
making these wastes my time?

282
00:14:24,785 --> 00:14:26,186
