00:26:47,706 --> 00:26:48,825
Then whose fault is it?

572
00:26:50,265 --> 00:26:51,146
Go now.

573
00:26:51,745 --> 00:26:52,426
Right away.

574
00:26:52,866 --> 00:26:53,386
Mr. Zheng.

575
00:26:54,226 --> 00:26:56,146
Actually, I don't think it's a big deal.

576
00:26:56,386 --> 00:26:58,466
It's a new era,
and people are free to love.

577
00:26:58,666 --> 00:26:59,706
You're both single.

578
00:27:00,105 --> 00:27:02,265
If you like each other,
isn't that great?

579
00:27:02,426 --> 00:27:03,666
Who said I like her?

580
00:27:06,345 --> 00:27:07,505
Who said I like her?

581
00:27:07,785 --> 00:27:08,946
If not,

582
00:27:09,105 --> 00:27:10,426
then why did she bring you meals?

583
00:27:10,785 --> 00:27:11,626
How would I know?

584
00:27:12,626 --> 00:27:14,825
I had no idea when
she developed such fleeting thoughts.

585
00:27:16,065 --> 00:27:18,505
Mr. Zheng, you didn't get it.

586
00:27:19,545 --> 00:27:21,065
Listen carefully.

587
00:27:21,545 --> 00:27:25,105
These aren't just fleeting thoughts.
It's genuine affection.

588
00:27:25,666 --> 00:27:27,946
You can't devote your life to a city.

589
00:27:28,386 --> 00:27:31,065
It's time to consider your happiness.

590
00:27:31,666 --> 00:27:34,466
Even so, I couldn't consider her.

591
00:27:35,265 --> 00:27:38,406
She's young and I'm old.

592
00:27:38,585 --> 00:27:40,785
She might be ignorant, but I am not.

593
00:27:41,105 --> 00:27:42,906
Then make it clear to her yourself.

594
00:27:43,585 --> 00:27:45,906
If I could make it clear to her,
why would I need you?

595
00:27:46,226 --> 00:27:48,866
You know how high my blood pressure is.

596
00:27:50,386 --> 00:27:51,785
I did talk to her.

597
00:27:52,065 --> 00:27:54,226
I told her
to stop such absurd behaviors.

598
00:27:54,986 --> 00:27:55,825
She agreed,

599
00:27:56,146 --> 00:27:57,906
yet now, it's like she never heard me.

600
00:28:01,345 --> 00:28:04,226
Mr. Zheng, I want to help,

601
00:28:04,906 --> 00:28:06,466
but I am the mayor.

602
00:28:07,025 --> 00:28:09,825
It's inappropriate for me to
constantly meddle in personal matters.

603
00:28:11,706 --> 00:28:13,226
And frankly, I'm not good at it.

604
00:28:15,025 --> 00:28:16,025
Li Qiuping.

605
00:28:16,226 --> 00:28:19,226
I'm not speaking to you
as Zheng Decheng,

606
00:28:19,626 --> 00:28:21,585
but as the Secretary
of the town committee.

607
00:28:21,785 --> 00:28:24,226
I order you
to handle this matter properly.

608
00:28:25,025 --> 00:28:25,706
Is that clear?

609
00:28:26,386 --> 00:28:26,946
Mr. Zheng.

610
00:28:27,305 --> 00:28:29,025
I can't guarantee I could make it.

611
00:28:29,466 --> 00:28:30,146
I'll do my best.

612
00:28:30,825 --> 00:28:32,745
No way, you have to make it.

613
00:28:36,402 --> 00:28:39,314
(Chunmei Printery)

614
00:28:43,065 --> 00:28:43,706
Ms. Li.

615
00:28:45,906 --> 00:28:46,406
Lili.

616
00:28:48,626 --> 00:28:49,966
Mr. Zheng. Wait...

617
00:28:51,906 --> 00:28:52,406
Ms. Li.

618
00:28:53,426 --> 00:28:54,065
What's wrong?

619
00:28:54,825 --> 00:28:55,906
Why do you know I am here?

620
00:28:56,585 --> 00:28:59,065
I called your salon.
Your assistant said you'd be here.

621
00:29:01,825 --> 00:29:02,545
Hairstyle catalog.

622
00:29:03,146 --> 00:29:04,426
(Quality First)
I asked them to print it.

623
00:29:05,986 --> 00:29:06,745
What's wrong?

624
00:29:10,545 --> 00:29:12,545
I brought you the Picasso art book

625
00:29:12,745 --> 00:29:13,745
I mentioned.

626
00:29:14,505 --> 00:29:15,005
Thank you.

627
00:29:31,745 --> 00:29:32,866
Picasso is really amazing.

628
00:29:34,825 --> 00:29:37,505
He painted blue
with such depth and beauty.

629
00:29:38,505 --> 00:29:39,226
Yes.

630
00:29:42,585 --> 00:29:44,785
Lili, these hairstyles look great.

631
00:29:49,386 --> 00:29:51,386
What's wrong? Lacking inspiration?

632
00:29:52,226 --> 00:29:53,105
Something upsets me,

633
00:29:55,305 --> 00:29:56,585
so I can't focus.

634
00:30:01,745 --> 00:30:02,626
What is it?

635
00:30:13,186 --> 00:30:14,345
I can't tell anyone.

636
00:30:16,226 --> 00:30:17,426
It might get him in trouble.

637
00:30:18,946 --> 00:30:20,065
I won't tell others.

638
00:30:21,666 --> 00:30:22,386
Who is it?

639
00:30:32,065 --> 00:30:32,785
Mr. Zheng.

640
00:30:36,986 --> 00:30:37,825
Mr. Zheng?

641
00:30:38,186 --> 00:30:38,825
Mr. Zheng.

642
00:30:40,186 --> 00:30:42,626
Lili, what do you like about Mr. Zheng?

643
00:30:43,626 --> 00:30:46,906
He's so handsome and incredible!

644
00:30:47,065 --> 00:30:49,666
With broad shoulders and long legs,
he's so humorous.

645
00:30:49,785 --> 00:30:51,025
Everything he explains

646
00:30:51,265 --> 00:30:52,825
just clicks for me.

647
00:30:53,105 --> 00:30:54,505
Once I heard his big ideas,

648
00:30:54,946 --> 00:30:55,906
I would be

649
00:30:55,946 --> 00:30:57,025
giggling away like crazy.

650
00:30:57,305 --> 00:30:58,626
During class, he told us

651
00:30:58,825 --> 00:31:02,105
the story of raising turtles,
running for Secretary,

652
00:31:02,426 --> 00:31:03,745
and peeling shrimp for years.

653
00:31:03,906 --> 00:31:05,265
Peal one shrimp per second.

654
00:31:05,345 --> 00:31:06,186
Who can do that?

655
00:31:07,866 --> 00:31:08,386
He can.

656
00:31:08,666 --> 00:31:09,986
I think he's just incredible.

657
00:31:10,025 --> 00:31:11,426
There's nothing he can't do.

658
00:31:11,666 --> 00:31:14,186
And he dresses well.
The color combinations are spot on.

659
00:31:14,366 --> 00:31:16,545
I think everything about him
is perfect and incredible.

660
00:31:17,345 --> 00:31:18,626
You're with him every day.

661
00:31:18,785 --> 00:31:20,466
Don't you think
he's incredibly handsome?

662
00:31:20,505 --> 00:31:21,386
Don't you?

663
00:31:23,666 --> 00:31:24,226
Right.

664
00:31:25,105 --> 00:31:25,626
Right.

665
00:31:27,186 --> 00:31:28,146
I think,

666
00:31:35,025 --> 00:31:36,585
when you like someone,

667
00:31:38,226 --> 00:31:40,745
you should like everything about him
and know him inside out.

668
00:31:41,146 --> 00:31:42,426
Not just his strengths.

669
00:31:42,866 --> 00:31:44,545
The flaws are also part of a person.

670
00:31:45,545 --> 00:31:46,186
Otherwise,

671
00:31:46,585 --> 00:31:49,186
you'd become very blind.

672
00:32:03,025 --> 00:32:04,785
I did find one of his flaws.

673
00:32:06,745 --> 00:32:07,946
Because of this,

674
00:32:09,866 --> 00:32:11,265
I can't sleep for days.

675
00:32:12,265 --> 00:32:13,025
What is it?

676
00:32:13,505 --> 00:32:15,065
I thought he was perfect

677
00:32:16,146 --> 00:32:16,986
in every way.

678
00:32:18,866 --> 00:32:19,986
But he told me

679
00:32:21,706 --> 00:32:23,466
to keep my distance from him,

680
00:32:24,626 --> 00:32:26,265
so I could only stalk him.

681
00:32:27,065 --> 00:32:27,946
And I found out...

682
00:32:37,065 --> 00:32:38,105
His neck is crooked.

683
00:32:40,825 --> 00:32:42,025
His neck is crooked?

684
00:32:42,466 --> 00:32:43,226
His crooked neck.

685
00:32:44,906 --> 00:32:46,666
Didn't you notice that?

686
00:32:47,866 --> 00:32:49,585
You're with him every day.

687
00:32:49,866 --> 00:32:51,305
Didn't you notice that?

688
00:32:52,706 --> 00:32:54,866
It might be a tiny bit crooked.

689
00:32:54,866 --> 00:32:56,585
A tiny bit?

690
00:32:58,545 --> 00:32:59,866
It's seriously crooked!

691
00:33:02,146 --> 00:33:02,906
I asked myself,

692
00:33:03,146 --> 00:33:04,426
"What do you like about him?"

693
00:33:04,785 --> 00:33:05,865
"Do you like his neck?"

694
00:33:05,865 --> 00:33:07,626
"Do you like him or his neck?"

695
00:33:07,745 --> 00:33:09,126
I like him, right?

696
00:33:09,265 --> 00:33:10,946
Then why am I always
focusing on his neck?

697
00:33:11,305 --> 00:33:12,906
And ever since I noticed it was crooked,

698
00:33:12,946 --> 00:33:15,226
it just seems
more and more crooked to me.

699
00:33:15,245 --> 00:33:17,345
Now it's unbearable to me!

700
00:33:19,706 --> 00:33:20,505
Lili...

701
00:33:23,585 --> 00:33:24,866
What I want to ask is,

702
00:33:27,265 --> 00:33:28,785
how can I

703
00:33:30,186 --> 00:33:31,626
keep liking him

704
00:33:33,585 --> 00:33:34,745
but also ignore

705
00:33:37,105 --> 00:33:38,345
his crooked neck?

706
00:33:40,226 --> 00:33:42,345
Then I think you just don't like him.

707
00:33:43,666 --> 00:33:44,626
I don't like him?

708
00:33:44,986 --> 00:33:46,305
Right, you don't.

709
00:33:46,466 --> 00:33:47,146
Why?

710
00:33:48,065 --> 00:33:49,545
If you truly liked him,

711
00:33:49,706 --> 00:33:51,986
you wouldn't focus on his crooked neck.

712
00:33:52,186 --> 00:33:54,186
You'd overlook this little flaw.

713
00:33:54,666 --> 00:33:55,505
Can you?

714
00:34:03,466 --> 00:34:03,986
Exactly.

715
00:34:10,585 --> 00:34:11,946
So, I don't like him.

716
00:34:14,266 --> 00:34:15,386
You don't like him.

717
00:34:16,786 --> 00:34:19,466
Will he be sad if I tell him?

718
00:34:19,906 --> 00:34:23,225
No, he will understand you.

719
00:34:39,266 --> 00:34:40,946
Didn't I just take this yesterday?

720
00:34:40,946 --> 00:34:41,986
Why check again today?

721
00:34:42,105 --> 00:34:44,426
We need to monitor your blood pressure.

722
00:34:44,426 --> 00:34:45,705
Here then.

723
00:34:45,866 --> 00:34:46,366
Alright.

724
00:34:47,545 --> 00:34:48,545
Such a hassle.

725
00:34:49,866 --> 00:34:50,705
Put your arm on this.

726
00:34:54,906 --> 00:34:56,266
What difference could it make?

727
00:34:58,105 --> 00:34:59,665
I suspect you have hypertension.

728
00:35:00,466 --> 00:35:01,625
I'll monitor for three days.

729
00:35:05,225 --> 00:35:05,786
Just take it.

730
00:35:06,105 --> 00:35:06,625
Fine.

731
00:35:13,145 --> 00:35:13,786
Ms. Li.

732
00:35:14,025 --> 00:35:14,525
Mr. Zheng.

733
00:35:14,866 --> 00:35:15,545
Shut it.

734
00:35:16,145 --> 00:35:16,786
Shut it.

735
00:35:17,625 --> 00:35:18,665
High blood pressure again?

736
00:35:24,266 --> 00:35:24,906
Ms. Li.

737
00:35:26,065 --> 00:35:27,505
The task I assigned yesterday...

738
00:35:29,746 --> 00:35:30,246
Well...

739
00:35:32,705 --> 00:35:33,746
That person...

740
00:35:34,505 --> 00:35:35,025
Who?

741
00:35:35,786 --> 00:35:36,386
Shut it.

742
00:35:37,105 --> 00:35:37,605
Put it on.

743
00:35:39,505 --> 00:35:40,005
Well...

744
00:35:51,386 --> 00:35:51,986
What's wrong?

745
00:35:54,625 --> 00:35:55,746
Why are you staring at me?

746
00:35:56,466 --> 00:35:58,665
Once it's noticed,
it's really hard to overlook.

747
00:35:59,225 --> 00:36:00,786
What do you mean?

748
00:36:02,025 --> 00:36:03,065
I'm asking you

749
00:36:03,386 --> 00:36:05,426
if you make it clear to that person.

750
00:36:05,986 --> 00:36:07,826
Rest assured, I've clarified it.

751
00:36:08,105 --> 00:36:10,386
That person said it was
just a misunderstanding.

752
00:36:14,426 --> 00:36:15,585
A misunderstanding?

753
00:36:17,426 --> 00:36:19,346
Mr. Zheng, your blood pressure
is normal now.

754
00:36:24,025 --> 00:36:24,866
Mr. Qian,

755
00:36:26,266 --> 00:36:27,585
I feel like

756
00:36:27,906 --> 00:36:29,386
I've seen this

757
00:36:30,025 --> 00:36:31,306
(Super Dog Restaurant)
happen before.

758
00:36:32,986 --> 00:36:34,266
Not exactly.

759
00:36:34,746 --> 00:36:36,826
Back then, you just arrived.

760
00:36:37,145 --> 00:36:37,986
We weren't familiar

761
00:36:38,306 --> 00:36:41,386
with this new type of restaurant,
so nobody came.

762
00:36:42,826 --> 00:36:45,346
But now everyone's business
is struggling,

763
00:36:45,386 --> 00:36:48,466
so no one's coming.
There is a big difference.

764
00:36:50,705 --> 00:36:52,505
I've sold at cost price.

765
00:36:52,946 --> 00:36:54,466
Can't make it any lower.

766
00:36:54,466 --> 00:36:55,225
Right.

767
00:36:57,346 --> 00:36:58,705
With so few customers,

768
00:36:58,746 --> 00:37:00,705
just turn off some lights.

769
00:37:03,505 --> 00:37:04,105
I don't care.

770
00:37:05,665 --> 00:37:07,665
You asked me to come to Yuehai.

771
00:37:08,145 --> 00:37:09,025
Take responsibility.

772
00:37:10,145 --> 00:37:11,466
Otherwise, I have to move.

773
00:37:11,505 --> 00:37:12,225
Wait, come on.

774
00:37:12,466 --> 00:37:13,906
Don't be so anxious.

775
00:37:15,505 --> 00:37:16,225
Well, listen.

776
00:37:16,746 --> 00:37:18,585
Tomorrow I'll go to the town government

777
00:37:18,826 --> 00:37:20,605
and ask them
to think of a solution, okay?

778
00:37:21,705 --> 00:37:22,205
Okay.

779
00:37:23,625 --> 00:37:24,125
Well...

780
00:37:24,986 --> 00:37:26,545
I'm a bit hungry. Get me

781
00:37:26,746 --> 00:37:27,946
a roast duck rice meal, okay?

782
00:37:29,386 --> 00:37:30,225
Rice is available,

783
00:37:30,746 --> 00:37:32,585
but no roast duck.

784
00:37:32,685 --> 00:37:34,065
Wait, I just want a roast duck.

785
00:37:34,225 --> 00:37:34,826
No duck!

786
00:37:34,866 --> 00:37:36,105
I haven't eaten meat in days.

787
00:37:36,145 --> 00:37:36,826
No duck!

788
00:37:36,926 --> 00:37:39,545
Look, those ducks you have will go bad.

789
00:37:41,866 --> 00:37:42,625
Thanks!

790
00:37:49,386 --> 00:37:50,266
(Buy Three Get One Free)
Are you two eating?

791
00:37:50,746 --> 00:37:51,246
No.

792
00:37:51,306 --> 00:37:52,145
Okay.

793
00:37:53,138 --> 00:37:58,353
(Grand Sale! All Dishes 30 Percent Off.
Today's Special: 20 Percent Off)

794
00:38:19,065 --> 00:38:20,105
Yan.

795
00:38:20,585 --> 00:38:23,346
You spent so much money
on this karaoke machine,

796
00:38:23,625 --> 00:38:26,386
but with business struggling,
who's coming to sing now?

797
00:38:38,786 --> 00:38:39,306
Yan.

798
00:38:39,545 --> 00:38:40,065
Meng.

799
00:38:40,346 --> 00:38:42,306
- Ms. Li.
- Where are you off to?

800
00:38:42,946 --> 00:38:44,986
I am heading to the mall

801
00:38:45,225 --> 00:38:47,025
to return this karaoke machine.

802
00:38:47,665 --> 00:38:49,065
Return it? Why?

803
00:38:50,505 --> 00:38:52,266
I was too impulsive back then.

804
00:38:52,505 --> 00:38:54,665
The machine was only popular
for a few days.

805
00:38:55,025 --> 00:38:57,065
Now, hardly anyone comes to sing.

806
00:38:57,746 --> 00:38:58,246
And,

807
00:38:58,386 --> 00:39:00,625
even this big mall is empty now.

808
00:39:01,105 --> 00:39:03,665
Let alone this street.
There's no foot traffic.

809
00:39:03,866 --> 00:39:06,625
So I thought to return it.

810
00:39:06,826 --> 00:39:08,466
I'd lose money even if I sold it now.

811
00:39:08,665 --> 00:39:11,746
I bought it for 2,500 yuan,
now it's only worth 1,800 yuan.

812
00:39:12,225 --> 00:39:14,105
You're right. Better return it now.

813
00:39:15,145 --> 00:39:15,906
Don't.

814
00:39:16,185 --> 00:39:16,705
Yan.

815
00:39:16,946 --> 00:39:19,346
Do you know the economic theory
called the lipstick effect?

816
00:39:19,946 --> 00:39:22,346
When the economy faces difficulties,

817
00:39:22,625 --> 00:39:24,386
mass entertainment actually thrives.

818
00:39:26,826 --> 00:39:28,306
Lipstick effect?

819
00:39:28,906 --> 00:39:29,665
In other words,

820
00:39:29,946 --> 00:39:31,625
everyone's struggling to make money,

821
00:39:31,866 --> 00:39:32,946
so they're feeling upset.

822
00:39:33,746 --> 00:39:34,826
They actually need

823
00:39:35,065 --> 00:39:37,105
entertainment that can cheer them up.

824
00:39:38,306 --> 00:39:41,065
Anyway, don't rush to return it.
Just hold on.

825
00:39:41,585 --> 00:39:44,545
If no one sings, you sing yourself
to attract people.

826
00:39:46,065 --> 00:39:56,545
♪Fish are hard to catch,
taxes are heavy♪

827
00:39:56,746 --> 00:40:06,625
♪Fishermen are poor for generations♪

828
00:40:07,386 --> 00:40:17,225
♪The tattered fishing net
Grandpa left behind♪

829
00:40:17,665 --> 00:40:28,306
(Yan's Wontons)
♪It helps us survive another winter♪

830
00:40:28,466 --> 00:40:29,946
- Good!
- Good!

831
00:40:31,225 --> 00:40:31,746
Thank you.

832
00:40:32,545 --> 00:40:33,705
Thank you.

833
00:40:34,585 --> 00:40:35,266
One more!

834
00:40:35,505 --> 00:40:36,665
No more.

835
00:40:36,826 --> 00:40:38,906
The next song was requested
by Table Two,

836
00:40:38,906 --> 00:40:40,225
"Liu Hai the Woodcutter."

837
00:40:40,346 --> 00:40:41,826
- Good!
- Good!

838
00:40:42,906 --> 00:40:43,986
Sing with me.

839
00:40:44,225 --> 00:40:44,866
No problem.

840
00:40:44,906 --> 00:40:45,505
Great!

841
00:40:54,065 --> 00:40:54,565
Look.

842
00:40:54,866 --> 00:40:55,366
Let me help.

843
00:40:55,906 --> 00:40:56,505
You're swamped.

844
00:40:56,906 --> 00:40:57,746
Those two, right?

845
00:40:57,746 --> 00:41:01,185
♪Here I compare you♪

846
00:41:01,386 --> 00:41:04,946
(Fuyu Road Market)
♪To someone♪

